@node "HISTORY" "Version history"
v2.0    22-Dec-2010
    - modernized the internals, using most of the recommended new features
      of AmigaOS4.1
    - found the bug preventing help hint usage, they are fully supported now
    - added support for application.library messages
    - uses application.library PrefsObjects for preferences loading/saving
    - saves and optionally opens the last browsing position automatically
    - confirms exit if quitting with the edited but unsaved bookmarks
    - supports the yet-to-be-released French John Nelson Darby translation worked
      by Pascal Marcelin

v1.13   30-Oct-2008
    - added Edit/Copy menu item and gadget required by OS4.1 text.datatype

v1.12   06-Oct-2007
    - modified Autoinstall script, no actual changes in executable

v1.11   23-Sep-2007
    - corrected iconify code not to dispose icon too early and crash
    - added AutoInstall script for AmiUpdate

v1.10   22-Sep-2007
    - added support for for French LSG (Louis Segond) bible
    - added French catalog, thanks for Alexandre Balaban!
    - added compatibility code for AmiUpdate for future automated updates
    - now uses program's icon as iconify icon if available
    - remembers bookmark file name in ASL requesters
    - now uses SetVar/GetVar() to handle environmental var prefs file

v1.9    03-Mar-2007
    - release for OS4 only
    - using requester.class for information requesters
    - enhanced the window contents
    - uses AISS image set if available
    - added hierarchical bookmark list
    - added iconification support
    - added window history (remembers Bible, book or chapter changes)
    - the chapter and verse gadgets have maximum limits
    - menu items disabled if not available
    - more effective memory handling with Alloc/FreeVecPooled()
    - removed the type checking problem for localization/GetString()
    - bug removed: incompatibility with the new memory system
    - bug removed: using horizontal scroller book popup window could be opened
    - bug removed: crashed if Search selected clicked with no books selected
    - bug removed: crashed if no books loaded at startup but only later

v1.8    01-May-2006
    - added support for mouse wheel of Amiga OS4 prerelease update 4
    - modified the window title to contain the program name also
    - the included alternate PNG icons were contributed by Paul Bloedel
      and you'll need PowerIcons (or OS4+plugin) to actually see them

v1.7    06-Mar-2005
    - polished a couple of bugs concerning the start and exit phases of
      the program (OS4 version only)

v1.6    10-Oct-2004
    - recompiled for OS4 (the other executables are still v1.5)
    - support for PageUp/PageDown keys
    - catalog file got some changes

v1.5    20-Jan-2003
    - introduced support for German Luther Bibel (found in Aminet)

v1.4    27-Dec-2002
    - changed the former program name BibleView to BibVision
      due to name conflict with already existing commercial program
    - removed the Elberfelder file names from the database; the
      German version won't happen because the text are copyrighted
    - bugfix: the "Read settings" file requester's name buffer was
      too small, and one couldn't open the settings file there

v1.3    24-Nov-2002

    - introduced support for Swedish 1917 translation
    - introduced support for German Elberfelder translation;
      currently the bible texts seem to be removed from Funet,
      probably the copyright owner (http://www.brockhaus-verlag.de)
      doesn't want them to be spread; the executables don't contain
      any code for Elberfelder but if the copyright owner changes
      its mind, BibVision is ready (they haven't answered to my email)
    - modified the indexor routines so new translations can be added
      easily
    - enlarged the default sizes of Bible window and book chooser gadget
    - book chooser now remembers the last book chosen
    - bugfix: freed the indexed Bible name too early, so the
      requester text may have been trashed
    - bugfix: the Bible window text area is now always cleared before
      new book is opened in order to remove all previous book text
    - bugfix: SETTINGS command line/tooltype argument was never used
    - changed the email support address again

v1.2    13-Jul-2002

    - introduced CHAPTER and VERSE tooltypes
    - introduced Save BookMark menu item
    - bugfix: Finnish '92 Psalm number handling works now correctly
    - bugfix: removed icon handling problem, FreeDiskObject()
      would try to free wrong section of memory
    - reworked and modularized the code overall, the executable
      is much smaller now
    - new email and support home page addresses

v1.1    22-May-2002

Minor update:
    - corrected few typos in the manual file
    - corrected the contact information in About requester


v1.0    29-Apr-2002

Released finally. New features:
    - everything
    - probably some bugs
@endnode

